## Reading & Exploration

### Start with OVERVIEW.md

```sh
cat file.{{ ext }}@/OVERVIEW.md               # symbol table with token estimates
cat dir@/OVERVIEW.md                    # aggregated overview across a directory
```

### Read Specific Symbols

```sh
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process.{{ ext }}           # shorthand for body
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/body.{{ ext }}     # explicit form
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/signature.{{ ext }}   # declaration line only
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/docstring.txt  # docstring only
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/decorators.{{ ext }}  # attributes/decorators
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/imports.{{ ext }}            # import block
```

### Filter by Kind

```sh
ls file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/by-kind/fn/       # all functions
ls file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/by-kind/struct/   # all structs
ls file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/by-kind/impl/     # all impl blocks
```

### Line-to-Symbol Lookup

Given a line number (from diagnostics, grep, blame):

```sh
readlink file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/at-line/42    # zero-cost: discover which symbol
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/at-line/42         # follows symlink, reads the body
```

### Batch Reads

```sh
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/{Foo,Bar,Baz}@/body.{{ ext }}    # multiple symbols at once
cat file.{{ ext }}@/lines:10-20                        # raw line range (when needed)
```

### Hover Documentation and Hints

```sh
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/DOC.md      # hover docs and type info
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/HINTS.md    # inlay hints (inferred types)
```

