## Code Relationships (LSP-Powered)

**Use these instead of Grep for relationship queries.**

| What | Path | Use case |
|-|-|-|
| Callers (incoming) | `Foo@/CALLERS.md` | Before changing signature or behavior |
| Dependencies (outgoing) | `Foo@/DEPS.md` | Tracing what a function calls |
| All references | `Foo@/REFERENCES.md` | Before renaming, moving, or deleting |
| Definition | `Foo@/DEFINITION.md` | Where a symbol is defined |
| Declaration | `Foo@/DECLARATION.md` | Where a symbol is declared |
| Implementations | `Foo@/IMPLEMENTATION.md` | All concrete impls of a trait |

### Symlink Traversal

Each relationship has a symlink directory (`callers/`, `deps/`, `references/`).
Follow symlinks to traverse the codebase without resolving file paths:

```sh
# Read a caller's body — no need to know which file it lives in
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/callers/init.{{ ext }}

# Edit a caller directly through the symlink
Edit file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/callers/init.{{ ext }}

# Check actions available on a caller
ls file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/callers/init/actions/

# Chain traversal: Foo → callers → bar → deps
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/callers/bar/deps/baz.{{ ext }}
```

