## Editing

### Targeted Edits (Edit Tool)

Read first, then edit — Edit only sends the diff:

```
Read file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/body.{{ ext }}
Edit file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/body.{{ ext }}  (old_string/new_string)
```

### Full Rewrites (Bash)

```sh
# Rewrite a function body
cat <<'EOF' >file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/body.{{ ext }}
fn process(input: &str) -> Result<()> {
    validate(input)?;
    Ok(())
}
EOF

# Insert a new symbol after an existing one
cat <<'EOF' >>file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/body.{{ ext }}
fn process_batch(items: &[Item]) -> Result<()> {
    items.iter().try_for_each(process)
}
EOF
```

### Imports, Signatures, Decorators

```sh
# Append an import
echo 'use std::collections::HashMap;' >>file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/imports.{{ ext }}

# Replace an import
sed -i 's/{OldType, NewType}/NewType/' file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/imports.{{ ext }}

# Change signature without touching body
echo 'fn process(input: &str, opts: Options) -> Result<()>' \
    >file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/signature.{{ ext }}

# Add a decorator
echo '#[instrument]' >>file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/decorators.{{ ext }}
```

### Delete a Symbol

```sh
rmdir file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/old_helper@/    # splices out from source
rm file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/old_helper.{{ ext }}  # shorthand — same effect
```

### In-Body sed

```sh
sed -i 's/old_var/new_var/g' file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/body.{{ ext }}
```

All writes are **tree-sitter validated** — invalid syntax returns an error, never a broken file.

