## Batch Edit Staging

Stage multi-symbol edits, preview as a validated diff, apply atomically.

### Stage Edits

```sh
echo 'fn new_impl() { ... }' >file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/edit/replace
echo 'fn helper() { ... }' >file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Bar@/edit/insert-after
echo '/// docs' >file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Baz@/edit/insert-before
echo 1 >file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Old@/edit/delete

# Append as last child (impl blocks, modules)
echo 'fn method() { ... }' >file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/MyImpl@/edit/append
```

### Review Staged Actions

```sh
ls file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/edit/staged/               # list staged actions
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/edit/staged/10-replace.diff  # preview one
rm file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/edit/staged/10-replace.diff   # remove without applying
```

### Preview and Apply

```sh
# Per-symbol preview
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/edit/staged.diff

# Global preview (all files)
cat @/edit/staged.diff

# Apply all staged edits atomically
rm @/edit/staged.diff

# Clear without applying
> @/edit/staged.diff
```

Cross-file batch edits: stage in multiple files, preview with `cat @/edit/staged.diff`,
apply with `rm @/edit/staged.diff`.

