## Symbol Naming Conventions

| Pattern | Meaning |
|-|-|
| `symbols/my_function.{{ ext }}` | Top-level symbol (shorthand for body) |
| `symbols/Foo~Struct.{{ ext }}` | Disambiguated by kind (when Foo~Impl also exists) |
| `symbols/Trait_for_Type.{{ ext }}` | Trait/interface implementation |
| `symbols/Foo~Impl@/symbols/new.{{ ext }}` | Nested method inside impl block |
| `UPPERCASE.md` | Read-only metadata (generated on read) |
| `lowercase.ext` | Read/writable source content |

When names are ambiguous, `ls file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/` shows the exact filesystem entries.

---

## Anti-Patterns

| Anti-pattern | Correct approach |
|-|-|
| `Read file.{{ ext }}` (raw file read) | `Read file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/OVERVIEW.md` then targeted symbol |
| `Grep "fn process" src/` | `ls file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/by-kind/fn/` or `OVERVIEW.md` |
| `Grep "process" src/` for callers | `cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/CALLERS.md` |
| Full file read for imports | `cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/imports.{{ ext }}` |
| `cargo check` after edits | `cat file.{{ ext }}@/DIAGNOSTICS.md` (instant) |
| Editing raw source files | Edit `@/symbols/` bodies (tree-sitter validated) |
| Grep + manual line math for symbol | `readlink file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/at-line/42` (instant) |
| Reading N files for call sites | `CALLERS.md` has inline code context for all sites |
| Modifying without checking callers | **Always** read `CALLERS.md` first |

---

## Error Codes

| Error | Meaning | Action |
|-|-|-|
| `EINVAL` | Invalid input | Fix content: bad syntax, invalid UTF-8, stale target |
| `ENOTSUP` | Not supported | No decomposer for this language — edit source directly |
| `EIO` | System failure | Retry once; if persistent, report |
| `EACCES` | Permission denied | File is read-only |
| `ENOENT` | Not found | Re-read the parent directory or `OVERVIEW.md` |
